        <h2 id="karina-recipe1">Home Made Red Sauce Spaghetti</h2>
        
         <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/pasta.png" alt="Red Sauce Spaghetti" width="400">
         
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 40 mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 5 servings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Spaghetti</td>
                    <td>5 servings</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Ground Pork</td>
                    <td>1 pound</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Tomatos</td>
                    <td>3 each</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Onion</td>
                    <td>1 each</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sun-Dried Tomatos</td>
                    <td>3 table spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pasta Sauce</td>
                    <td>1 large jar</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Boil a pot of water to cook spaghetti.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Chop tomatos and onion.<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Add oil into a pan and start cooking ground pork for 3 mins.<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Add tomatos and onions into the pan and cook.<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> Pour pasta sauce and sun-dried tomatos into the pan and cook everything for 2 mins.<br>
        <strong>Step 6:</strong> Take cooked spaghetti from pot and add into the pan.<br>
        <strong>Step 7:</strong> Cook for another 1 min until the spaghetti soaks up the sauce then turn off stove.
            
        </p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://selfproclaimedfoodie.com/homemade-pasta/">Homemade recipes from Karina</a></em></p>
    <p><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>
    
    
    <h2 id="karina-recipe2">Very Berry Yogurt</h2>
        
         <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/berries.png" alt="Avocade Cobb Salad" width="400">
         
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 5 mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 3 servings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Strawberries</td>
                    <td>5 pieces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Black Berries</td>
                    <td>5 pieces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Blue Berries</td>
                    <td>10 pieces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Plain Greek Yogurt</td>
                    <td>2 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Honey or Syrup</td>
                    <td>2 table spoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Lemon Juice</td>
                    <td>1 table spoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Wash all the fruits and dry them with paper towels.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Chop the fruits into smaller pieces.<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Pour the fruits and greek yogurt into a big bowl.<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Add honey or syrup into the bowl.<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> You can add some lemon juice into the bowl if you like a little sour taste.<br>
        <strong>Step 6:</strong> Mix everything together.<br>
        <strong>Step 7:</strong> Serve the very berry yogurt in small bowls.
    </p>
    
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/berry-yogurt-cups/">Very Berry Yogurt</a></em></p>
    <p><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>
    
    
    <h2 id="karina-recipe3">Chocolate Granola Bars</h2>
        
         <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/chocolates.png" alt="Chocolate Granola Bars" width="400">
         
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 15 mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 5 servings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk Chocolate Bar</td>
                    <td>1 piece</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>White Chocolate Bar</td>
                    <td>1 piece</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Dark Chocolate Bar</td>
                    <td>1 piece</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Dried-Fruits</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Unsalted Mixed Nuts or Granola</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Boil a pot of water and put another small bowl inside the pot.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Break chocolate bar into smaller pieces.<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Put chocolcate into the small pot inside the big pot to cook until melt.<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Grab a baking pan or chocolate mold and pour the chocolate into the pan or mold while it is still hot.<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> Add mixed nuts and dried-fruits to the top of the chocolate that you just poued.<br>
        <strong>Step 6:</strong> You can pour different types of chocolate into the same pan or mold to create multi-color chocolate bars.<br>
        <strong>Step 7:</strong> Put your chocolate pan or mold into refridgerator to cool it down.<br>
        <strong>Step 8:</strong> When the chocolate is fully cooled and hardened, now you have your homemade chocolate granola bars.
    </p>
    
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1013622-granola-bars-with-chocolate">Chocolate Granola Bars</a></em></p>
